    "Sourness is detected through the protonation of hydrogen ions, which directly influence ion channels.",
    "Saltiness and some aspects of sourness are mediated by epithelial sodium channels (ENaCs).",
    "In addition, transient receptor potential (TRP) channels also play an important role in mediating responses to certain tastants and temperature-related sensations, especially for bitter and spicy compounds (Deepankumar et al. 2019).",
    "Taste perception is not confined solely to the tongue; it is significantly enhanced by retronasal olfaction, a process where volatile compounds from food travel to the nasal cavity, thereby enriching and complicating the gustatory experience.",
    "This interaction illustrates the profound link between taste and smell, as flavor perception is inherently a multisensory process."
